view.attribution: NYC Department of Housing Preservation and Development (HPD)

columns.name: BUILDING_ID
columns.description: The Building ID is a unique numeric identifier assigned to each building by HPD.

columns.name: BOROUGH
columns.description: The Borough is the borough where the building is located.

columns.name: NUMBER
columns.description: The House Number is the street number in the building's address. E.g, the house number is '100' in '100 Gold Street.'

columns.name: STREET
columns.description: The Street Name is the name of the street in the building's address. E.g, the street name is 'Gold Street' in '100 Gold Street.'

columns.name: TOTAL_UNITS
columns.description: Total Units reflects the number of units in the building as of the report run date and may vary from the unit count reported when the building was selected for the AEP program. HPD records indicated that all the buildings had at least three dwelling units at the time of selection.

columns.name: AEP_START_DATE
columns.description: The date the building was selected for participation in the AEP. All buildings in a particular round will have the same start date.

columns.name: # OF B/C VIOLATIONS AT START
columns.description: The count of hazardous and immediately hazardous violations open on the date the building was selected for participation in the AEP.

columns.name: CURRENT_STATUS
columns.description: "Active" buildings are currenty participating in program. "Discharged" buildings have met a statutory requirement for removal from the program.

columns.name: DISCHARGE_DATE
columns.description: The date the building was removed from the program.

columns.name: AEP_ROUND
columns.description: The round identifies a group of buildings selected for the AEP annually.

existing_fields.Agency: Department of Housing Preservation and Development (HPD)

view.description: Each year, the Department of Housing Preservation and Development (HPD) designates severely distressed multiple dwellings for participation in the Alternative Enforcement Program (AEP). HPD is required by law to submit and post an annual summary report of all AEP buildings. This dataset includes all buildings selected for participation in the AEP and the current status of the building in the program.
